metadata.name: Canyon #105
metadata.description:
Canyon is a generative art project inspired by canyons and reinterpreted in 9 different styles (that each have their own specificities):
- Grand Canyon
- Radioactive
- Blue Grotto
- Black Crystals
- Magma
- Iceberg
- Imagination
- UV
- Sandstone

Accessories (Kayak, Rowing Boat, Barrels) are present on some variations (in this case, it is possible to generate a second variation without accessories by pressing "a").

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Interlaced #15
metadata.description:
From African tribal clothes to Islamic mosaics every civilization throughout history has produced delicate patterns to share the essence of their culture. These artifacts have changed our understanding of how art, like societies form through bonds, the very fabric of things that have become symbols for cycles, paths and relationships.

Interlaced explores these unique motifs using emergent algorithms to produce colorful continuous patterns. The project uses a dynamic engine that traverses triangular meshes placing diverse tile configurations. By combining art with technology, the project aims to tell a new story of making digital connections between geography, culture and time.

Press “s” to save in high-resolution.

metadata.name: one hour #64
metadata.description:
`one hour` is an interactive installation exploring the bond between humans and computers, inviting you to pause and share a meditative moment with an algorithmic stranger.

Rather than conventionally interacting with the piece, lower your guard and allow it to interact with you through an intimately human connection - a heart beat. `one hour` follows this heart as it beats through an hour of its enduring existence, captured by an EKG divided into 60 rows of 60 seconds each. Stylistically, it emulates realistic paper and ink using custom texture and line renderers. The piece will play through the duration of the hour, pause for five minutes, then begin anew.

`one hour` was created for a physical installation, projected to a wall and animated in real time. By default it will render at high speed to reveal the preview. For the most immersive experience at home, it should be viewed in full screen and adjusted to real time speed (controlled via the number keys).

||| controls

[s] save as png
[r] reset animation
[l] toggle looping [default on]
[1-5] adjust render speed
[--1] real time (1 hour) [recommended]
[--2] 6x (10 minutes)
[--3] 60x (1 minute)
[--4] 300x (12 seconds) [default]
[--5] full speed

metadata.name: musical society #688
metadata.description:
society.png: musical society is a collaborative PFP work drawn by Tito Yusuf and directed by Sandy Pirouzi with the aim to facilitate Tezos newcomers with affordable PFP to rock.

This series is taking inspiration from a music scene that Tito is part of. Some traits are paying tribute to some of Tezos musicians such as Jburn, Musical Jackal, Binerica, and Sigmun.

---------------------------------------------
  Most will be us
Some are pretending to be us
Some others are even not us
(And few of them are not even alive anymore)
---------------------------------------------

  PS Tito is a master at bad drawing. Don’t expect fine lines with perfect alignment in his drawing (but the colors are fun!).

  PPS There’s no utility in this project except the CC0 license, so just have fun with it ;)  

Special thanks to:
 purespider for the template and assistance
Jburn, IndraAziz (Musical Jackal), Binerica, Mirffu (Sigmun) for allowing the making and usage of respective traits
ciphrd and fx(hash) team for allowing the making and usage of fx(hash) traits

 Type: Image Composition
 Dimension: 1000 x 1000 px
License for visual: CC0 
License for code: MIT

Twitter: @titoys90 @spirouzi

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #125
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Unicorn #6041
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.
